Everest Re Says Japan Quake May Cause Losses of $320 Million

-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 
2011-04-12T21:26:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/everest-re-says-japan-quake-may-cause-losses-of-320-million.html
Everest Re Group Ltd. (RE) , the Bermuda-
based insurer and reinsurer, said the earthquake and tsunami
that struck  Japan  last month will cost about $320 million.  The forecast assumes losses for the industry of $25
billion, Everest Re said today in Business Wire statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Frye in New York at 
 afrye@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  